history.narrative: Law 9-236, the “Animal Control Amendment Act of 1992,” was introduced in Council and assigned Bill No. 9-306, which was referred to the Committee on Human Services. The Bill was adopted on first and second readings on December 1, 1992, and December 15, 1992, respectively. Signed by the Mayor on December 31, 1992, it was assigned Act No. 9-368 and transmitted to both Houses of Congress for its review. D.C. Law 9-236 became effective on March 17, 1993.
